3 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 11-103.6f,
4 is amended to read as follows:
5 Section 11-103.6f. A. Prior to September 1, 2003, the State
6 Board of Education shall adopt rules to ensure that students who
7 transfer into an Oklahoma school district from out of state after
8 the junior year of high school of the student shall not be denied,
9 due to differing graduation requirements, the opportunity to be
10 awarded a standard diploma.
11 B. The rules shall allow district boards of education to make
12 exceptions on an individual student basis to the high school
13 graduation requirements of Section 11-103.6 of this title for such
14 students who would be unable to meet the specific graduation
15 requirements without extending the date of graduation. Each
16 district board of education that grants exceptions pursuant to this
17 subsection shall report to the State Department of Education on or
18 before July 1 of each year the number of students granted exceptions
19 and reasons for the exceptions.
20 C. By December 1, 2015, the State Board of Education shall
21 adopt rules requiring school district boards of education to waive
22 the Oklahoma history high school graduation requirements of Section
23 11-103.6 of this title for children of military families as defined
24 in the Interstate Compact on Educational Opportunity for Military
Req. No. 17183 Page 43

1 Chil dren, set forth in Section 510.1 of this title, who transition
2 with the military from another state and who have satisfactorily
3 completed a similar state history class or other one-half unit or
4 set of competencies in history or citizenship skills in another
5 state. The school district board of education may also waive the
6 Oklahoma History high school graduation requirements for a student
7 who meets the criteria provided in this subsection if the student
8 completes a project or writes a paper, without the assistance of
9 artificial intelligence, subject to approval of the school district,
10 that demonstrates competencies and knowledge of Oklahoma history or
11 United States Government.
